pported, and eligible for nearly all major \n        welcome bonuses at Irish-facing casinos.\n      </p>\n\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong>Instant deposits</strong> to activate bonuses and promotions.</li>\n        <li>Accepted at almost every reputable Irish-friendly casino.</li>\n        <li>Simple, secure checkout using your existing debit or credit card.</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <p>\n        The main drawback is that card withdrawals can be slower than other options. Many casinos redirect payouts \n        to e-wallets or bank transfer instead of sending funds back to your card, which can extend processing times.\n      </p>\n\n      <h4>Best For</h4>\n      <ul>\n        <li>New players making their first deposit</li>\n        <li>Quick access to welcome bonuses</li>\n        <li>Players who prefer familiar, straightforward payment flows</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <h4>Potential Downsides</h4>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Some banks may block gambling-related transactions</li>\n        <li>Withdrawals can be slower and may redirect to bank transfer</li>\n        <li>Possible foreign exchange fees at non-EUR casinos</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <p>\n        Cards are ideal for starting out, but many Irish players prefer faster withdrawal methods \u2014 \n        such as Skrill, Neteller or crypto \u2014 for long-term use.\n      </p>\n\n      <!-- ONLINE BANKING / ACH -->\n      <h3>Bank Transfers &amp; Instant Banking \u2014 Reliable EUR Withdrawals</h3>\n\n      <p>\n        <strong>Bank transfers and instant online banking services</strong> remain among the most stable withdrawal \n        methods for Irish players. These options link directly to your bank through secure regulated systems and \n        are supported by most major casino brands operating in the Irish market.\n      </p>\n\n      <ul>\n        <li><strong>Strong security</strong> with bank-level verification.</li>\n        <li>Clear withdrawal timeframes published by reputable operators.</li>\n   